Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Trim,
then thinly slice @scallions{1}(trimmed and sliced), separating greens and whites.
Cut @mushrooms{8}(sliced into thin slices, about ¼ inch thick).

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing occasionally, until browned
and a little crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}. Remove from pan and transfer to a
#paper-towel-lined plate{}. Rinse out pan and wipe dry.

Once water boils, add @fusilli{about 250g} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Scoop out 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Lower heat under pan used for mushrooms to medium and add @butter{2%tbsp}(plain).
Once melted, add scallion whites and cook until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Add @flour{1%tbsp} and stir to combine. Cook, stirring often, until flour loses
its raw smell, about ~{2%minutes}. Whisk in @milk{6.75%tbsp} and ⅓ cup pasta
cooking water, making sure to eliminate any flour clumps. Let simmer until
slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @cream cheese{2%tbsp} to pan and stir to melt, then stir in mushrooms and
fusilli. Stir @garlic herb butter{2%tbsp} into pan. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

> Everything should be coated in a loose, creamy sauce. If very thick, add more pasta cooking
> water 1 TBSP at a time until desired consistency is reached.

Divide pasta between plates and sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup}.
Garnish with scallion greens and serve.